 Former Italian Prime Minister, Silvio Berlusconi, has died. He was 86. According to Italian media, Berlusconi died at the San Raffaele hospital. He was treated for a lung infection linked to a previously undisclosed chronic leukaemia in April. Read also: EU offers Tunisia over €1bn to stem migration In 2016, Berlusconi had an open-heart surgery. His health hasn’t been in the best shape after after he contracted COVID-19 three years ago. Berlusconi first came to office in 1994 and led four governments until 2011. He led the centre-right Forza Italia party which went into coalition under Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni after elections in September, when he was elected to Italy’s upper house, the Senate.